### 5\. Create skill directory

#### `plugins/core/skills/skogai-testing/SKILL.md`

```markdown
---
name: skogai-testing
description: bats-based testing skill for bash hooks and scripts. use when writing tests, testing hook scripts, validating shell functions, or setting up bats test suites.
---

<objective>
test bash hooks that read JSON from stdin, produce JSON on stdout, and
communicate via exit codes. provides helpers, patterns, and conventions.
</objective>

<quick_start>
1. write a .bats file under tests/hooks/
2. load test-helper: `load ../test-helper`
3. use hook helpers: `run_hook`, `make_hook_input`, `assert_json_field`
4. run: `argc test` or `bats tests/hooks/*.bats`
</quick_start>

<hook_testing_pattern>
hooks receive JSON on stdin and output JSON on stdout.

```bash
input=$(make_hook_input '{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"rm -rf /"}}')
run_hook "$HOOK" "$input"
assert_exit_code 2
assert_stderr_contains "BLOCKED"
```

available helpers (from tests/test-helper.bash):

| helper | purpose |
| -- | -- |
| `make_hook_input '{"overrides":...}'` | build JSON envelope with session_id, cwd, etc |
| `run_hook "$script" "$json"` | pipe JSON to hook, capture stdout/stderr/status |
| `assert_exit_code N` | exact exit code check |
| `assert_json_field ".path" "value"` | jq field equals value |
| `assert_json_has_field ".path"` | field exists and not null |
| `assert_valid_json` | output parses as JSON |
| `assert_stderr_contains "text"` | stderr includes string |
| `assert_stderr_not_contains "text"` | stderr excludes string |

standard bats helpers also available:
`assert_success`, `assert_failure`, `assert_output_contains`, `assert_output_equals`,
`assert_file_exists`, `assert_dir_exists`, `setup_test_dir`, `teardown_test_dir`,
`setup_git_repo`, `skip_if_missing`
</hook_testing_pattern>

* one .bats file per hook: `test-.bats` in `tests/hooks/` - always setup_test_dir in setup, teardown_test_dir in teardown - test both allow (exit 0) and block (exit 2) paths - validate JSON structure for hooks that produce output - run via `argc test` (all) or `argc test hooks` (hooks only)

<test_layout>

```
tests/
  test-helper.bash          # assertions + hook helpers
  hooks/                    # hook test files
    test-pre-tool-use.bats
    test-session-start.bats
    test-stop.bats
    test-marketplace-json.bats
  examples/                 # bats pattern reference
    example-function-tests.bats
    example-file-tests.bats
    example-git-tests.bats
```

</test_layout>

<success_criteria>

- [ ] `argc test` runs all bats tests and exits 0
- [ ] [pre-tool-use.sh](<http://pre-tool-use.sh>) blocks all 9 dangerous patterns
- [ ] [session-start.sh](<http://session-start.sh>) produces valid hookSpecificOutput JSON
- [ ] marketplace.json passes schema validation
  </success_criteria>

